      <hedline>
        <hl1>It's Time to Talk About Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James Siegel letter says Americans will not understand climate change until religion and science are accepted as separate and distinct systems of examination; drawing (Sept 28 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Time to Connect the Dots'' (editorial, Sept. 28) does not mention a simple fact about a dynamic climate change: there are too many Americans willing to throw a religious shroud over science.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Time to Connect the Dots'' (editorial, Sept. 28) does not mention a simple fact about a dynamic climate change: there are too many Americans willing to throw a religious shroud over science.</p>
        <p>Until we as a country accept science for what it is (a data-driven system for exploring what can be measured) and religion for what it is (a faith-based system for exploring what cannot be measured), we are more likely to color than connect the dots.</p>
        <p>James Siegel  Portland, Me., Sept. 28, 2005</p>
      </block>
